<br>
 It's late July, and the sun is setting as I walk into my summer hut in Kelethin. The moon has never been so bright since the mining started, so I decided to take my concert there and maybe see some sights with a few friends. Summer of Hope has been good so far, I think I'm really starting to gain a following since my last album. The more recent songs are very flighty and light on the brain if you wanna call it that.<br>
<br>
 Pulling my boots off, I wiggle my toes, making them pink again. Loose moon dust falling to the bare wooden floor makes me think of fairy dust and magical powders.  Am I even awake?  Momma always taught me that I should always organize myself before heading to bed. Always examine your backpacks after long trips and hunting expeditions in case a critter gets into your food supply. So I empty my bags on top of my bed and sift through the papers, runes, coin, and other odd treasures. My fingers trace a couple of old letters and pictures.<br>
<br>
 I still carry his picture. Why can't I just get over him? Leaning my head back against the bedpost, I start to go into a deep gaze.  <br>
<br>
 I got &quot;my official letter&quot; exactly 17 days ago. <br>
<br>
 To be honest, I really expected it. <br>
<br>
 War is harsh. Why is there so much hate when there is plenty of loving to be had?  That's why I went to Firona Vie, where we placed our marriage papers in a join vault.  I went to the registrar responsible for surnames and put in an application to change my name.  <br>
<br>
 &quot;Hopeful Warsong. That's me&quot;<br>
 <br>
 &quot;Maughan Warsong. Deceased.&quot;<br>
<br>
 When I had to explain that to this lady, I felt so numb. Like part of me was laying cold, face down in the snow off the cliff in Cobalt Scar, where they had found him...<br>
<br>
 &quot;My profession, ma'am?&quot; &quot;Oh, sorry I forgot to fill in that spot...&quot;<br>
<br>
  What's the point, I thought.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Musician&quot; I told her. &quot;I'm actually just passing through Kunark, I'm on tour.&quot;<br>
<br>
  Touring for what? Him? He's dead, Hope. Get over it.<br>
<br>
  <br>
Crickets chirp below in the thicket under my treetop getaway.  My agent stops in to give me my tour agenda for the next month. It's going to be a long summer I can see. Many many trips in Velious and Luclin... God, not Velious...<br>
<br>
  Tell me there's something more out there for me. <br>
<br>
  For now, I'm Hopeful Lovesong.  Pouring my heart out through song to everyone who could use it.  Love songs. Heh. Can I get some of that? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
